00:19:52,092 --> 00:19:55,260
your aura is this
dingy, pasty, gray...

292
00:19:55,362 --> 00:19:57,763
I don't believe in auras.

293
00:19:57,864 --> 00:19:59,965
Yeah, you don't
believe in anything.

294
00:20:00,066 --> 00:20:04,336
Oh, well, I'm sorry I can't be as
high-strung and crazy as the rest of you.

295
00:20:04,437 --> 00:20:05,804
I'm sorry, too.

296
00:20:05,905 --> 00:20:09,208
I wish you would be
high-strung and crazy for once

297
00:20:09,209 --> 00:20:11,410
instead of keeping all your
feelings bottled up inside.

298
00:20:11,411 --> 00:20:13,178
She just called your aura dingy.

299
00:20:13,179 --> 00:20:14,346
Are you gonna take that?

300
00:20:14,347 --> 00:20:15,781
What do you want from me?

301
00:20:15,882 --> 00:20:19,685
You want a teary confession
about how hard my childhood was?

302
00:20:19,786 --> 00:20:21,120
Well, it wasn't.

303
00:20:21,221 --> 00:20:24,223
I was a rich only child
who got anything I wanted

304
00:20:24,324 --> 00:20:26,592
as long as I behaved...

305
00:20:26,693 --> 00:20:28,861
And sat still

306
00:20:28,962 --> 00:20:31,563
and didn't speak
unless spoken to.

307
00:20:31,664 --> 00:20:34,466
My mother said I had
to keep out of trouble.

308
00:20:34,467 --> 00:20:36,969
We had my dad's political
career to think about.

309
00:20:36,970 --> 00:20:38,837
Well, that's it, then.

310
00:20:38,838 --> 00:20:41,674
You had a controlling mother
who had certain expectations

311
00:20:41,675 --> 00:20:43,776
and if you strayed from them
you were shut down.

312
00:20:43,777 --> 00:20:46,078
That's why you're afraid
to care about anything

313
00:20:46,079 --> 00:20:47,246
and why you can't
express yourself.

314
00:20:47,247 --> 00:20:49,615
You want me to express myself?

315
00:20:49,716 --> 00:20:50,983
Leave me alone!

316
00:20:53,019 --> 00:20:55,621
I like it when you
express yourself.

317
00:20:55,722 --> 00:20:56,855
Don't touch me.

318
00:20:56,956 --> 00:20:59,024
I'm still mad at you.

319
00:20:59,125 --> 00:21:02,461
My life hasn't been
that easy, either, mai.

320
00:21:02,462 --> 00:21:05,330
Whatever- that doesn't excuse
the way you've been acting.

321
00:21:05,331 --> 00:21:06,899
Calm down, you guys.

322
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,501
This much negative energy
is bad for your skin.

323
00:21:09,602 --> 00:21:11,070
You'll totally break out.

324
00:21:11,171 --> 00:21:12,221
Bad skin?

325
00:21:12,305 --> 00:21:14,807
Normal teenagers worry
about bad skin.

326
00:21:14,908 --> 00:21:16,308
I don't have that luxury.

327
00:21:16,409 --> 00:21:20,179
My father decided to teach me
a permanent lesson on my face.

328
00:21:20,280 --> 00:21:22,047
Sorry, zuko, I...

